Definition.WordDefinition: Brand-new \Brand"-new"\, a. [See {Brand}, and cf. {Brannew}.] Quite new; bright as if fresh from the forge. [1913 Webster]
brand-new adj : conspicuously new; "shiny brand-new shoes"; "a spick-and-span novelty" [syn: {bran-new}, {spic-and-span}, {spick-and-span}]
